Also realized `Panel` uses the [`hidden` attribute](https://github.com/mui/base-ui/blob/master/packages/react/src/tabs/panel/useTabsPanel.ts#L54) when not active, so Tailwind 4's reset could interfere with exit animations, since it applies:
```css
[hidden]:where(:not([hidden='until-found'])) {
    display: none !important;
}
```

Hi guys, I found a working approach for animating `Tabs.Panel` with Motion.

```tsx
function TabsPanel(props: BaseTabs.Panel.Props) {
  const { value, ...otherProps } = props;
  const isOpen = value === useTabContext().value;

  return (
    <AnimatePresence initial={false} mode="popLayout">
      {isOpen && (
        <BaseTabs.Panel
          key={value}
          value={value}
          keepMounted
          hidden={false}
          render={(props) => {
            const { className, ...otherProps } = props;

            return (
              <motion.div
                className={cn(
                  "data-[activation-direction=right]:[--starting-x:100%]",
                  "data-[activation-direction=right]:[--ending-x:-100%]",
                  "data-[activation-direction=left]:[--starting-x:-100%]",
                  "data-[activation-direction=left]:[--ending-x:100%]",
                  className,
                )}
                initial={{
                  opacity: 0,
                  x: "var(--starting-x)",
                }}
                animate={{
                  opacity: 1,
                  x: 0,
                }}
                exit={{
                  opacity: 0,
                  x: "var(--ending-x)",
                }}
                transition={{
                  type: "spring",
                  stiffness: 200,
                  damping: 22,
                }}
                {...(otherProps as any)}
              />
            );
          }}
          {...otherProps}
        />
      )}
    </AnimatePresence>
  );
}
```

But I tried to animate `BaseTabs.Panel` natively with the built-in data attributes, but I couldn’t get it to work as expected.

```tsx
<BaseTabs.Panel
  data-slot="tabs-panel"
  className={cn(
    "transition-all duration-300",
    "data-ending-style:opacity-0 data-starting-style:opacity-0",
    "data-starting-style:data-[activation-direction=left]:translate-x-[-100%]",
    "data-starting-style:data-[activation-direction=right]:translate-x-[100%]",
    "data-ending-style:data-[activation-direction=left]:translate-x-[100%]",
    "data-ending-style:data-[activation-direction=right]:translate-x-[-100%]",
    className,
  )}
  {...otherProps}
/>
```

Does anyone know how to make this work?

